{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pydantic/pydantic/issues/585","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pydantic/pydantic","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pydantic/pydantic/issues/585/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pydantic/pydantic/issues/585/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pydantic/pydantic/issues/585/events","html_url":"https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic/issues/585","id":454145570,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0NTQxNDU1NzA=","number":585,"title":"Feature request -- no-alias constructor","user":{"login":"m-burst","id":3243475,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyNDM0NzU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3243475?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst","html_url":"https://github.com/m-burst","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/m-burst/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":14,"created_at":"2019-06-10T12:27:45Z","updated_at":"2019-10-07T17:40:02Z","closed_at":"2019-10-07T17:40:02Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"# Feature Request -- no-alias constructor\r\n\r\nImagine the following model:\r\n\r\n```py\r\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\r\n\r\nclass MyModel(BaseModel):\r\n    my_field: int\r\n\r\n    class Config:\r\n        fields = {'my_field': {'alias': 'myField'}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow, I want to do the following:\r\n\r\n* Deserialize input data, which is currently done as `MyModel(**data)`, where `data` is a dict like `{'myField': 1}`\r\n* Create instances of `MyModel` using Python attribute names in order to serialize them, e.g. something like `MyModel(my_field=1).dict(by_alias=True)`\r\n* And do the above two points without having to enable `allow_population_by_alias` to avoid introducing subtle bugs, as specified in the docs.\r\n\r\nAs far as I see, this could previously be done via `MyModel.construct(my_field=1)` but the signature of `construct` was changed so that this now leads to less clear code (`MyModel.construct({'my_field': 1}, {'my_field'})`).\r\n\r\nI'm not sure yet how this could look in the API (maybe a new classmethod?), and I'm not sure that I'm not the only one concerned with this problem, but it would be great to hear from you on this.\r\n\r\nThanks in advance!","closed_by":{"login":"samuelcolvin","id":4039449,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQwMzk0NDk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4039449?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin","html_url":"https://github.com/samuelcolvin","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samuelcolvin/events{/privacy}","received_events_